document_data.Description:
{{Quote
|Before opening a sarcophagus, light a torch.
|[[X the Mystic]]'s 7{{th}} [[Rules of Dungeon Survival|rule of dungeon survival]]
}}
These wooden implements often had one end covered in a cloth (or [[flax]]) that was doused with a flammable substance. They were popular with adventurers that explored dark avenues and darker dungeons.

As well as being used as a source of light, torches or fire sources equivalent to torches were used as [[material component]]s in [[spell]]s such as ''[[chariot of Sustarre]]'' and ''[[fire lance]]''. They could also be used as bludgeoning [[weapon]]s that might also ignite foes.

document_data.Powers:
{{Quote
|A flaming stick of wood. Ancient humanoids feared the dark, and the monsters it hid, until they invented this marvel.
|Adventurer's torch
}}
There were several [[magic]]al torches across the [[Realms]]. The gateway to [[Deepearth]] from the [[Bloodstone Mines]] had torches that could not be put out by normal methods, and even had a very high resistance to magic.

A torch could be turned into an ''[[infratorch]]'', a torch that enabled those within its "light" radius to see as if they had infravision.
